HEADWORD: Anolis
<hw>A*no"lis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[In the
Antilles, <ets>anoli</ets>, <ets>anoalli</ets>, a lizard.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of lizards which belong to the family
<fam>Iguanid⟦ae⟧</fam>. They take the place in the New World of the
chameleons in the Old, and in America are often called
<altname>chameleons</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
